not tied to the threat posed by violent extremism, but rather my skin and clothes When I was 14, for the first time I shaved my arm pits. As a teenage girl growing up in a beautiful place stranded in a tumultuous situation, I felt liberated when my sisters showed me how to hide the excess hair using make-up. It was really just a matter of time before I hit puberty, which came with acne, the dreaded V of hair that in East Timor, where Christian missionaries had a strong presence, the unequally distributed hair on our bodies was deemed ugly by people around us and by myself.

Undeniable Freedom

Our History Formed by history, anointed by political struggle, & fueled by peace, determination & self-awareness—the nation of Timor-Leste (formerly East Timor) is an invigorating program that brings refreshing knowledge and perspective to the world. The country exploded into headlines following a dramatic struggle for independence and its varied history will prove an exciting addition to any curriculum in sociology, global studies, and government. Suitable for middle school to college, our comprehensive program must include: History–The program starts with a chronicle of Timor's harsh occupation by Portuguese colonists and subsequent brutal takeover by Indonesia. Contemporary society–Geography, government, religion, history, surroundings, family and traditions are all presented along with a comprehensive timeline.
